ing of fingerprints. This is a developmental question. It is the randomness of how cells migrate and the timing of gene expression that dictates. Each cell will either express from both alleles of a gene or there will be gene choice. The choice however does not need to be the same for each and every cell in a tissue. So where a cell ends up in development and whether it is expressing Maternal, Paternal, or both alleles determines"}],"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b10de963b115fd0720d6a558fd1ac06c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":10456,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10456/march-ho","reputation":5867,"display_name":"March Ho","accept_rate":80},"score":24,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/b10de963b115fd0720d6a558fd1ac06c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":10456,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/10456/march-ho","reputation":5867,"display_name":"March Ho","accept_rate":80},"score":1,"post_id":34334,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/z6Tze.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15789,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15789/gordon","reputation":68,"display_name":"Gordon"},"edited":false,"creation_date":1431952815,"comment_id":54921,"body":"@Gordon That would be somewhere around <a href=\"http://www.prb.org/Publications/Articles/2002/HowManyPeopleHaveEverLivedonEarth.aspx\" rel=\"nofollow\">108 billion<\/a> which has a collision probability of approximately <a href=\"http://davidjohnstone.net/pages/hash-collision-probability\" rel=\"nofollow\">0.1%<\/a> assuming a fingerprint is used."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1MUb2.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1306,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1306/terdon","reputation":9339,"display_name":"terdon","accept_rate":73},"score":5,"post_id":34334,"reply_to_user