.com/avatar/2529c7a350c7665df3acdcd073f75167?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":13093,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/13093/steve-bond","reputation":324,"display_name":"Steve Bond"},"score":0,"post_id":28395,"edited":false,"creation_date":1423315930,"comment_id":46608,"body":"Sorry for putting this in the Answer box, but I don&#39;t have enough rep to comment yet... Can you please post the contents of your stockholm file as well? Also, just to be 100% clear, you are using BioPerl for your conversion, yes?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f437d9a11deebd214089822c26197f35?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3553,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3553/james","reputation":4533,"display_name":"James","accept_rate":83},"score":1,"post_id":28395,"edited":false,"creation_date":1423320304,"comment_id":46585,"body":"This looks like you are running clustalw with bioperl. I have answered assuming the original alignment is wrong. Could you post your original alignment, and what versions of these are you using?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1MUb2.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1306,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1306/terdon","reputation":9339,"display_name":"terdon","accept_rate":73},"score":0,"post_id":28395,"edited":false,"creation_date":1423322899,"comment_id":46591,"body":"Please show us the sequences you are attempting to align. They look like low complexity regions which are very hard to align but we can&#39;t judge without seeing the originals."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/eb116b84b6ebb26f58fb444b06ca0f4e?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":13373,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/13373/je-b","reputation":156,"display_name":"je_b"},"score":0,"post_id":28395,"edited":false,"creation_date":1423343076,"comment_id":46618,"body":"Yes, I am using Bi