 things at a higher resolution.<\/p>\n","answer_id":41451,"question_id":41448,"up_vote_count":3,"last_edit_date":1450007042}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/41448/does-neural-network-in-brain-form-cycles","last_activity_date":1450007042,"creation_date":1449917856,"answer_count":1,"title":"Does neural network in brain form cycles?","body":"<p>In other words is it possible for dendrite of neuron A to be connected with axon of neuron B and at the same time dendrite of neuron B to be connections with axon of neuron A (or similarly for any larger number of neurons)?<\/p>\n\n<p>If so, are there any statistical data on number of such cycles in average human brain?<\/p>\n","question_id":41448,"tags":["neuroscience"],"score":5,"accepted_answer_id":41451,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":53,"up_vote_count":5},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/uonSZ.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15272,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15272/lightweaver","reputation":740,"display_name":"lightweaver","accept_rate":43},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","reputation":26721,"display_name":"Christiaan","accept_rate":93},"score":10,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/uonSZ.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":15272,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/15272/lightweaver","reputation":740,"display_name":"lightweaver","accept_rate":43},"score":0,"post_id":41292,"edited":false,"creation_date":1449495861,"comment_id":69978,"body":"Couldn\u2019t the fetus have obtained fluids from the placenta (mother\u2019s plasma)?"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/1YczA.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":9943,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/9943/christiaan","r